{"title":"What I’ve been reading","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/905786123/0/marginalrevolution~What-Ive-been-reading.html","date":1728279189000,"content":"<p>Fiona Maddocks, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Goodbye-Russia-Rachmaninoff-Fiona-Maddocks/dp/1639365931/ref=sr_1_1?crid=B8BPEYMI27QL&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.-vK7iG7TN1cd5N-JyVCpmzrWfaakFMoO8coV4Ezciynn4BLk9_ipt_eFxsUFHp5vlm7g1iH7nm0TuV5irKqNI_tdOrjSu4n8zWz6RjzLjV_GsOKVVqO822Z0qpFQ1iVFj1_3jkbOLDzVt_hntGqScj1UcoYLcDCqUbNL4XMZdI3LoM1L27xPyLMzT6XnFiY7bOOQA61iTuRuYYvWhLVuGpgKdDWi0INyCZco5lWFeRA.IjDwFcU1PsTwBWpM3HHP4UZVd7Lp3XIsZwmmQv_krNE&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Fiona+Maddocks&amp;qid=1728257335&amp;sprefix=fiona+maddocks%2Caps%2C195&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Goodbye Russia: Rachmaninoff in Exile</a>.  Captures the spirit of the man and his music, and a good addition to the growing literature on European cultural exiles in America.  Readable and to the point.</p>\r\n<p>Kurt Weyland, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Democracys-Resilience-Populisms-Threat-Countering/dp/100943246X/ref=sr_1_1?crid=2XN8G7W1N1CQG&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.rMRo5OVNygT3ziWMGFWbDMk88_OcixuUv8HDq_dszh0.JJQw2B3_xqvKXpKCh3hg2_9pooGnpDN0QaLkpmVDB1M&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Democracy%27s+Resilience+to+Populism%27s+Threat&amp;qid=1728257376&amp;sprefix=democracy%27s+resilience+to+populism%27s+threat%2Caps%2C111&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Democracy’s Resilience to Populism’s Threat</a>.  This book has useful data, and perhaps it is a useful corrective to the most extreme fears out there.  But overall it does more to persuade me of the opposite conclusion, namely that populism is a real threat.  the author himself writes: “In fact, wide-ranging statistical studies find that only in about one-third of cases have populist chief executives done substantial damage to democracy. and they have truly suffocated liberal pluralism only in approximately one-quarter of all instances…”</p>\r\n<p>Richard J. Evans, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Hitlers-People-Faces-Third-Reich/dp/0593296427/ref=sr_1_1?crid=Z9QATIN5SZ0V&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.NkM_RGg_1FL6Pt-2-nDlUBVc1ZDfJACQZY7gzv0tvjNfb6laKqT1D22cNVus1hZJenMhFMP2Lf4WPsiMunIC7QvNe1-U1hAYLXmSPVzNLKokYwzFb46LOupotYQQGtAWlNu0IXN1KkkQSJ9TK87NBMgb6DW7ClHPlN4Y4on244v5euuLzhtxWbXF3hg9QNpsz7j-vzJILeskVJEP23v2Yw.1KmJD1bzWjgTjwKocxUpmkxAQLS-xwL1v_3idNbSNSU&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Hitler%27s+People%3A+The+Faces+of+the+Third+Reich&amp;qid=1728257482&amp;sprefix=hitler%27s+people+the+faces+of+the+third+reich%2Caps%2C98&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Hitler’s People: The Faces of the Third Reich</a>.  This very well-reviewed book does not seem to have either new data or new theory, as yes it does show a lot of the Nazis were “pretty ordinary people.”  Yet it is so well-written and well-presented that it deserves a high recommendation nonetheless.</p>\r\n<p>Tim Lankester, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Inside-Thatchers-Monetarism-Experiment-Promise/dp/1447371356/ref=sr_1_1?crid=3PY3A7OQKHF47&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.nJHjYA0zZMCwbUygHR9Ibg.bCFarOE8InMKm9NqQg6oaK04S7v4g7uAFFyQ532kYNY&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Inside+Thatcher%27s+Monetarism+Experiment&amp;qid=1728257541&amp;sprefix=inside+thatcher%27s+monetarism+experiment%2Caps%2C108&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Inside Thatcher’s Monetarism Experiment: The Promise, The Failure, The Legacy</a>, the author was on the scene in the Thatcher government.</p>\r\n<p>Michael Huemer, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Progressive-Myths-Michael-Huemer/dp/B0DFCK4WWB/ref=sr_1_1?crid=1IZ9F9L2TZS46&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.rYSKjEB3kMg6JFrkLDWIhg.bhNyZgSMFdbWnhgrZy8l8Ol2ijAxeHokvzlZFEwgOp0&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Michael+Huemer%2C+Progressive+Myths&amp;qid=1728257674&amp;sprefix=michael+huemer%2C+progressive+myths%2Caps%2C105&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Progressive Myths</a>.  Michael is a very smart philosopher, but this book seemed like a waste of time to me.  Will it persuade anyone?  Do we need Michael writing seven-page essays rebutting various claims of the BLM movement and the like?</p>\r\n<p>Josephine Quinn, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/How-World-Made-West-History/dp/059372979X/ref=sr_1_1?crid=38I4R8P51BVRV&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.TlOEVJhJi1YIGhnl6nLyfRbZrfZlsuiWVNQQyKwC5-w154gW7UTfoVw7DQPF77hH1xOPaXZ1tOPntrmAIZTGqWXM3_CxTC84AZHD6AeXQ06xheexSa_oqqYBiFhTaLkbLVlu1X9tL_PNWA6e7y14FK1F8U9HdESpi5tp_F1YKOjqMRk7zXyR03AWN024g-oRlALJsDdZE6z_7BRZ3jdejgXWe-tNAQCCG9ILcYpI0Jo.nb4Hb8Xo2FBiNqyBQOHfyBvTThdsHH9TWj4Lm0e8MbY&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=How+the+World+Made+the+West&amp;qid=1728257719&amp;sprefix=how+the+world+made+the+west%2Caps%2C106&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">How the World Made the West: A 4,000 Year History</a> is too chatty/friendly a book for me, but for many readers it is probably worthwhile.</p>\r\n<p>Ben Yagoda, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Gobsmacked-British-Invasion-American-English/dp/0691262292/ref=sr_1_1?crid=UHPAL47W3N6J&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.kUfzrfNPHSPdA09Yv0kAZA.x2XQyYH4zP7C4qzqesX5CPGJVvRDtMsSRiPMnOHmJmE&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Gobsmacked%21+The+British+Invasion+of+American+English&amp;qid=1728257770&amp;sprefix=gobsmacked+the+british+invasion+of+american+english%2Caps%2C118&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Gobsmacked! The British Invasion of American English</a> is great fun, either to read or to browse.  I do for instance use some of these words: <i>one-off</i>, <i>go missing</i>, <i>curate</i>, <i>early days</i>, <i>kerfuffle</i>, <i>easy peasy</i>, and <i>cheeky.</i></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Dana-Gioia-Critic-John-Zheng/dp/0881469564/ref=sr_1_1?crid=3L16UQ1DKUJAN&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.yajT2FQtW0V5jyXC9Aqwcw.V2NKMVOKfFgReybAOp2fnIpg4Xpif0z7UZKRo7L-SZA&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Dana+Gioia%3A+Poet+%26+Critic&amp;qid=1728257897&amp;sprefix=dana+gioia+poet+%26+critic%2Caps%2C91&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Dana Gioia: Poet &amp; Critic</a>, edited by John Zheng and Jon Parrish, is a series of essays in honor of Dana and a very good introduction to his life and work.  Here is my earlier CWT with Dana, information billionaire and aspiring information trillionaire.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Weep-Shudder-Die-Opera-Poetry/dp/1589881966/ref=sr_1_1?crid=2PJ67UL80ZK15&amp;dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.Bq4_M4n_-_6Cjg3oDReBHg.pkJod4MrOngUkbDCy6zTreCDilaMOVX7hbITAq71pKc&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=Weep%2C+Shudder%2C+and+Die%3A+On+Opera+and+Poetry&amp;qid=1728257965&amp;sprefix=weep%2C+shudder%2C+and+die+on+opera+and+poetry%2Caps%2C110&amp;sr=8-1\" target=\"_blank\">Weep, Shudder, and Die: On Opera and Poetry</a>, is Dana’s forthcoming book on opera.  He claims that Sweeney Todd is one of the two greatest American operas.</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/10/what-ive-been-reading-260.html\">What I’ve been reading</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/905786123/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/28/905786123/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/fblike20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/29/905786123/marginalrevolution,\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/pinterest20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_